content: Terrible now used to be my goto. Looking for new app now. Keeps adding dozens of quantity to sideboard on every deck. Random cards sometimes. Other times just ups wua tity fro. 3 to 39 or 51. Weird.

Please fix the card pics and please would you fix the pricing (it's been going on way too long).

Great app until I upgraded my phone. No longer seeing most pictures. Plus all the decks I created disappeared. I wish there was a fix for it. I contacted the developers, but no response unfortunately.

Ok.. bought the app and add on through Google play. Cant get a key for windows because i didn't purchase through paypal. The app is not great... and if you click on support or FAQ links is brings you to a file not found page... horrible Chinese programming... dont waste your money

Great app, great features, highly intuitive design and a garbage fire of a playtest mode. Seriously half my hand disappeared while I was scrolling to check my battlefield. Please fix this because this is not an ok problem to have.
App always worked fine and lately all card art is bugged and will not load. Please fix this asap!

Great app, comes with some quirks. It hasn't always been that way and I think the app just got updated or the database got updated bc some cards aren't showing the artwork. Also, it keeps adding multiple copies of cards in my sideboard (funny enough withstand death being one of them). I wish the test deck option was a little more robust but all around great app!

I paid for the premium version of Decked Builder many years ago. Earlier this year, like many Magic players, I got into MTG Arena due to not being able to play in person (not that I had enough players anyway lol). I sent an email to the devs about adding an "Historic" filter to the app, and the response was a solid "eventually" Well, I dont know how long the Historic filter has been active in the app, but I noticed it last week, and I can't appreciate a dev that listens, enough. THANK YOU!

Just updated this review (still 5-star). This is hands-down the best MtG resource on any app store. The database and search functions are expansive, and the interface is easy to use. Updates to the card database and restriction list are available almost immediately, and the ability to build, save, upload, and test decks brings this app over the top. Well worth the money, and kudos to the developers!
No longer able to price collection? What happened? Otherwise this should be a 4 star app.
Good for deck building but has a few hiccups every now and then. Could a format template be included? It would be nice to choose your commander and such.
Crashes when I look at cards after card search and when I open the deck tab. The decked builder trial app works better. Hope they fix it. Asking for a refund.

Fantastic app for deck building and goldfish testing, in fact the best... So long as it isn't night time. It's 2020, all apps should at least have the option of a dark mode! Obviously cards can't be effectively darkened, but the glaring white UI and my desire to deck build at night are at odds. If it weren't for that, I'd give this 5 stars all day long.

Great app, but stopped working since a few days. Update: and suddenly now is fixed. Off the naughty list again.
It's everything you would want in a deck building app.

Changing my review: As soon as I sent a message, I saw amazing communication via email with responses from the same person everyday. They worked hard to get the problems resolved by making changes daily. They kept me updated and would request for me to try the newest of changes as they were made. ...and it is working! (on my birthday, to beat all). This is my favorite app over all the others! It is a very clean and straight forward. It is the perfect tool to enhance Magic in my daily life.

At this point, I've given up. I lost years of deck lists.

A lot of people are giving 1-star reviews because of an update breaking the app. This is due to the deck files having been moved from com.deckedbuilder.decks to com.deckedbuilder.deckedbuilder.files.decks. I'm a developer myself so I could easily move these files on my own, but it should not have to be required. The developers should consider adding a first-step migration task to move files from the old storage location. All in all a great app, but this is kind of a blunder.

content: I just paid for the app and have been trying to use it because all of my magic teammates have been using it for years. I have a Google Pixel 2 XL. I don't believe the app is very compatible for this device. I can't make more than one deck without manually taking every single card entry back out of the deck. I even tried uninstalling and the original deck was still showing up. The new deck function didn't work at all. Very displeased. Hope this can be fixed. I was really looking forward to using.

to everyone who lost decks this week if you can get the decks back. use the import deck setting, hit the show internal storage button (mine was in the top right), select your phone as the search location, open Android folder, data, com.deckedbuilder, decks all lost decks should be there. you can import them and save them as the new deck format.

Off the bat, the base app is the list price and features around searching or viewing cards. If you want the library feature then it's an additional purchase.  I don't know about other apps, but this one needs a lot of work around usability managing your card, or creating decks.  Going from search card, to add to collection (the additional purchase mind you) and continue is a terrible experience and adding just 50 cards took me 2 hours through this interface and I hated it afterwards.  Deck management needs a lot of work around mana curve, deck stats, etc. Building a deck from collection needs to check the card is actually available as you can add any number of a card even if you only have one.  If this is the best app (no #8 paid app based on play stores stats) then heaven help us.  I hope the developer continues to make this better and that it becomes awsome in future or worth the price paid at the very least.

Other times it will crash and exit completely, and I've learned to always save my decklist before actually deckbuilding because of this.  Search options are alright, significantly worse than Gatherer and disorganized but acceptable for basic deckbuilding.  The pricing sources would be a great addition, if it ever worked for me. Either they take forever to load or just don't even bother loading at all. Testing the deck is difficult because of how sensitive swiping cards is. Barely touch the screen the wrong way and the whole board is ruined. This isn't a major problem but it's really jarring to swipe from card art to text only and back to card art again. Additionally, thumbnails take up far too much space and changing the thumbnail directory to an external SD doesn't work at all. Overall this app is full to the brim with bugs and annoyances (there's more, I don't have room for all of them). All the important parts work, but the rest feels incomplete/poorly implemented. Not worth paying for it IMO.

This app has been amazingly useful to me. I'm able to carry reference of my entire collection with me whenever I go to shops, toy with deck building any time I feel the urge, and easily find out when I purchase new cards wether or not I already have them in my collection.   The only two real frustrations I have with the app is that the play-test doesn't allow for testing against another deck (but it is still useful to gain a feel for how a deck is likely to play,) and that cards reissued as promotional cards do not have the option to add them as the promo card, but rather only as the original set's release.   I realize that the first is a rather large undertaking, and as the primary function of this app is deck building/collection management, I cannot fault the developers for this. The second, however, does leave me wanting improvement, as it affects the accuracy of the collection management aspect of the app.    I have however dropped my rating to three stars from 5 as the app now crashes regularly when attempting to load the deck management tab. This is rectified only by removing and reinstalling the app. While I'm still able to use the deck function after doing so, eventually the bug reappears and I have to go through the deletion process again.  Another star had been lost because in addition to the deck-view causing the app to crash, now viewing individual cards also causes the app to shut down. I have had to uninstall and reinstall the app every time I have gone more than 24 hours between uses for the past month and a half.  It is endlessly frustrating that the app that does everything I want to manage my decks and collections requires so much extra effort just to allow it to function.

Works great on my tablet. Would like to see auto complete implemented on the name search field. Other then that no complaints from this 19 year MTG veteran.

This application only works in upright. If you rotate your device it doesn't change. This should be a basic feature. Run on an android tablet it's absolutely awful.   Fix the app for tablet or landscape *or* mark it as incompatible with tablets so people don't download a broken app.
No landscape or tablet mode.
Great!!!  I use this all the time.  Get it.  You won't be disappointed.

This app is great, I love using it to track my deck builds.
for all my magic needs

Love it!
I love this app. One thing I would like to see would be an option for Commander deck building. That would earn a 5 star rating.

I've made so many decks with this, its really good. Search for keywords, and find cards you didn't know even existed. More sorting options would be appreciated (seperate the spell types when viewing deck), but the ability to email the deck makes up for it. Definately worth the download!

I bought this app mainly for deck testing. From my experiences thus far, I am not dissatisfied, but I do feel that in the actual testing windows, there should be a 'Shuffle Deck' button for those instances where you need to shuffle your deck, such as when you hit a bad Ponder and do not wish to keep the revealed cards. If added, it would make this a 5 star app.
Use this for my fantasy decks, keeps track and shows all the artwork

used it to inventory my MTG collection ...unless I missed something, would be nice to have a deck build within this app that allows to create your 60 card deck by pulling out of the cards you already have. other than that I think this app rocks
Would recommend this app to anyone. Including my wife...and that is saying a lot. Lol.

Awesome,  fast and practical.  Now I just need that they implement the collections to be perfect.
Best MtG app on the market! I've used several others, and this is by far the fastest loading, with the best UI. Great app!
This is the best deck building app I've used, including the defunct deck forge. I'm getting a few crashes on jelly bean, but I have submitted crash reports, and I'm sure they will be cleared up soon.
Absolutely fantastic app.

This app has helped me tremendously. The deck builder is easy to use and understand quickly. The prices are from lots of different websites and even includes stores on MOTO. The card search is a tad clunky, bu it works well. Its mainly used for finding a specific card and not just browsing for a type of card. But it works well. Overall, a very good and useful app. Definitely a buy.
Like the title says, this is the best deck app I have ever messed with. Keep it up, guys.

Finally a search engine that isn't retarded. I loved using Decked Builder on the IOS, and am happy they made it for the droid market. It was the one app that kept me as an IOS customer for so long. I've even debated switching back to the IOS JUST for this app. I've purchased every MTG collection, deck builder, search engine, etc. app on the droid market and none come close to Decked Builder. To put it short, I prefer searching for MTG cards in this order: Decked Builder, Wizards' Gatherer, then all else.
Works great, can even allow my fiancee, who is new to magic, to make her own custom deck. Easy to use and a great all around app.

It allows me to add all my cards I own in a nice organized list. Very organized... Well worth it if you're a huge fan. I also use it to take my whole collection anywhere and everywhere with no worries at all about damaging my cards. Trading is easy with others and double cards are stacked so it doesn't take up room when scrolling. I can build a deck I desire, ( even though I can buy the cards through this app ) I can take it to my local magic store and support them! Nice app.  Wish it had life counter tho.

I also have this app installed on my iPad and MacBook pro, all of which provide a slightly better experience, but all of the tangibles are here. Great job developers!! I'm very happy you have branched out to the Android Market, as I primarily use my android mobile devices over my iOS devices. I'd you couple provide an app for PC, I'd be even happier.

For me, this took the place of using MTG Tutor AND MTG Deck Forge. Well worth the money. It is such a great app. Search, Build, Test, Evolve or Revamp, Rinse & Repeat, Purchase, PWNAGE! All in one app! Uhm, why are you still reading this? You won't find the purchase button here. Go. Go now! :-)
Great.  Only wish it wasn't a problem to top or future sight in the tester besides that it is worthy to be my first paid app
Great! Love that there is pictures, searches, and a deck build that prices it with different sites.

Absolutely fabulous app. This is the best deck building app since DeckForge, worth every penny. The scans are gorgeous, the interface is clean and simple, and the test feature means you can theoretically play a full game with nothing more than two instances of this app. Obscenely recommended.
Loved it on my old iphone. So glad to see it here. Best by far.
This was the single best magic deck building app on the iPhone, and they finally brought it over for us Android users after WOTC sued to remove their deck building feature.  Thank you!!!
Excellent app. it serves the very purpose it was made for, making my magic deck

This is by far the most used app on my phone. Runs great even on my less-than-beefy HTC Wildfire S. Database is cached, so you can perform searches without needing a data connection. And the deck testing feature is not to be underestimated! Very useful for goldfishing a new brew. And the multiple card pricing sources? Just icing on the cake.
So great, I paid again for Android version.  I tried & paid for most others, both Android & Apple versions, but they can't compare to FEATURES, SPEED & STABILITY of Decked Builder !
The search functions which include searching cards by game format are awesome. Add to that the locally stored card database and this app is a keeper!
This is by far the best deck building app on the Android. Fast searching, deck sorting, pricing and even deck related news feeds. Light years ahead of everyone else.
